Revert "drm/i915/psr: Allow PSR with VRR on Panther Lake"
https://github.com/CachyOS/linux/commit/d60fc36b2cd461401ffd268210b04b5cd1162546

This reverts commit 29d9286d42dd22731cc15fcffc570ef142dbe1dc.

While PSR+VRR seems to work on Panther Lake, it doesn't on Lunar Lake
(and likely extends to other platforms that don't always use VRR TG).

When VRR TG is used, PSR can be used when VRR is on fixed refresh rate
mode, this is implied when setting crtc_state->vrr.enable:

	if (intel_vrr_always_use_vrr_tg(display))
		crtc_state->vrr.enable = vrr_enable && !intel_vrr_is_fixed_rr(crtc_state);
	else
		crtc_state->vrr.enable = vrr_enable;

So vrr.enable is true only when the display is using "true variable"
VRR, which is still unsupported by upstream. Revert this commit until
there is a better way to use PSR+VRR on compatible hardware (check for
always used VRR TG, DMI quirk table?).

Signed-off-by: Eric Naim <dnaim@xxxxxxxxxx>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
index 49b462aec85269..c8c5ee2205f736 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
@@ -1723,6 +1723,12 @@ static bool _psr_compute_config(struct intel_dp *intel_dp,
 	if (!CAN_PSR(intel_dp) || !display->params.enable_psr)
 		return false;
 
+	/*
+	 * Currently PSR doesn't work reliably with VRR enabled.
+	 */
+	if (crtc_state->vrr.enable)
+		return false;
+
 	entry_setup_frames = intel_psr_entry_setup_frames(intel_dp, conn_state, adjusted_mode);
 
 	if (entry_setup_frames >= 0) {
